story.title: Text Nerdy to Me - Episode 8
story.storyDescription: A wild night in Vegas results in a tryst she can’t remember, and a man she can’t forget.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Sabrina York is the New York Times and USA Today bestselling author of snarky, steamy romance.

story.prePaywallNotification: Erin should be glad she broke up with Charlie, right? Tap back into Hooked to find out what’s bothering her.
story.postPaywallNotification: Erin’s single and Will wants her…so tap back into Hooked to find out what happens next.

messages.text: Erin spends that night and most of the next day deep in contemplation.
Many of her thoughts revolve around Will.
That evening, Erin decides that she isn’t going to text him.
Erin! I had a great time on our date yesterday.
But I meant what I said.
I can’t just be your booty call.
So if that’s why you’re calling me—
There’s something else I have to tell you.
Charlie came over right after I got home last night.
I thought about what you said all the way home.
That’s not the way I want my future to be.
And what do you want for your future?
I want the kind of connection we shared.
But on the same token, I need to be cautious.
Apparently, I have a tendency to nest, or so my friends tell me.
I have no idea what that means.
When I meet a guy I like, I hunker down.
I tend to commit too quickly and then, when I doesn’t work…
So I want to take this slow.
I want to make sure we do this right.
Okay. So we’ll take this slow — together?
Because…I like the way I am around you.
Yeah. Because I feel like me when I’m with you too.
Exactly. I’m excited about, well, everything when I’m with you.
What kind of tone of voice is that?
Come on. I’m sexy and you know it.
But that doesn’t mean that voice is.
So what comes next? Are you…going to ask me out again?
I dunno. I thought it was your turn.
All right. Excuse me Will, but will please you go out with me?
Let me think about it for a—yes.
But this time, each breath they take pulses with sexual tension.
How do you propose I, ahem…entertain myself?
Mmm. Let me see. I bet I have an idea.
What? I’m pretty sure you used that line with me.
I thought for sure you would have…
Slipped into something even more comfortable.
I was thinking more along the lines of a thong.
How is a thong more comfortable?
You’re ruining the fantasy here, pumpkin face.
I’m wearing a lace bra, stiletto heels…
I have to get all dressed up and you’re in sweats?
What do you want me to wear?
Um…You could dress up like Jon Snow…
Fur cape. Valyrian steel sword. Moody but sultry expression…
Okay, yes — I’ve thought this through once or twice.
Which is why I like you.
You know what I would do if you were here right now?
I would lead you into the room, slowly.
The lights would be low and there’d be sexy music playing.
I don’t remember sexy music in GOT.
It’s okay. We might need to diverge from the cannon a little.
That was a test — I don’t like Country.
I lead you to the sofa.
We sit and I lean in…
You sigh as I trail my fingers along your arm.
Are you going straight for the boobs?
Will leads Erin through a world of pleasure…
Now that they know and understand each other more acutely.
Will and Erin moan and sigh over the line.
Then a comfortable, warm silence settles between them.
Yeah, because I heard your voice this time.
It was almost like being together…in person.
Maybe we could do that soon?
Good thing we have that date tomorrow.
You know, I’m so glad we met.
It’s strange, how it all happened though.
I know. What are the odds some other chick would randomly write my number on your arm?
Are you sure we haven’t met before?
You just looked so familiar when we DID meet.
Maybe it will come to you in time.
Maybe I saw you in my dreams somewhere…
Yeah. You probably saw me at Starbucks.
Do you go there a lot?
